Q>
You are solving a classification problem with a highly imbalanced class. The majority class is occurring 98% of times in the training data.
Now when you come with predictions, your model has 98% accuracy on test data. True in such a case are:
    1. Accuracy metric is not a good idea for imbalanced class problems.
    2. Precision and recall metrics are good for imbalanced class problems.
    
Q>
What is f1 score ?
Ans>
Harmonic mean of precision and recall 
